page.title: 20ECOLOGY AND TRAFFIC
page.content: {WILDFLOWERS IN VICINITY OF THE CASTLE. BUTTERCUP,SPEEDWELL, FOX TAIL GRASS DUTCH CLOVER, COW PARSLEY, RED CAMPION FOXGLOVE, RAPE,DOG ROSE, POPPY, MOON DAISY, RYE GRASS, SHEPHERDS PURSE, PHEASANTS EYE, GREATER STITCHWORT, FORGET ME NOT, DANDYLION, NETTLES, SCARLET PIMPERNEL, RAGWORT, SELF-HEAL, BROOM, PINEAPPLE MAYWEED. {TREES IN FIELDS NEAR TO CASTLE. } OAK, BEECH, ASH, ALDER, ELDER, APPLE, WILD CHERRY, SILVER BIRCH, ELM, HAZEL, LARCH, FIELD MAPLE, SYCAMORE, HAWTHORN, BLACKTHORN, SALLOW, HOLLY. {TRAFFIC SURVEY IN ROUNCIL LANE. } TIME 10.50-11.50AM. TOWARDS KENILWORTH- 7 CARS, 5 VANS, 1 LORRY, 1 TRACTOR, 1 MINI-BUS. TOWARDS BEAUSALE 4 CARS, 3 VANS, 16 MALE DRIVERS, 6 FEMALE DRIVERS. MOST POPULAR COLOURS WERE BLUE,YELLOW AND WHITE. OLDEST VEHICLE 5YRS OLD.
